<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-625-555  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 625 555.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 9 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comsat wins emergency phone contract. (along with Bell Atlantic'scellular phone group) (from Defense Communications Agency'sDefense Commercial Communications Office)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bell Atlantic Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    BEL.andO;Topic:     Cellular radioMobile PhonesContractsMobile Radio SystemsUnited States. Defense Communications AgencyTelephone systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMSAT WINS EMERGENCY PHONE CONTRACT 11/09/90 WASHINGTON, D.C., U.S.A., 1990NOV 9 (NB) -- Comsat and Bell Atlantic's cellular phone group announced theyhave won a contract to create a new system which will provide emergency phoneservice to the government during a natural disaster.andP;  The NationalTransportable Telecommunications Capability will be leased in an emergencyand provide satellite service in the Ku- band, linked by a ground station toa digital phone switch and cellular phones working on microwave frequencies.andM;Comsat will link the system to the public phone network, while Bell Atlanticwill provide the cellular phone network.andP;  It will be available for lease inJanuary, and field-tested later.andM;The work is being done under a contract awarded by the Defense CommunicationsAgency's Defense Commercial Communications Office as the acquisition agentfor the National Communications System.andP;  The system can be set up in 24hours, and fits inside a single C-130 cargo aircraft.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19901109/Press Contact: Comsat, John F. Gulick,202/863-6182; Bell Atlantic, Brian Wood, 908/306-7508)</TEXT></DOC>